If you haven't yet installed your new copy of iLife '11, then DON'T!!!

There are very many stories in the relevant Apple Discussions forum that point to widespread problems of a very serious kind, most of them having to do with the iLife '11 installation process and/or the Library update process that occurs when you first open your photo Library(ies) with the new version of iPhoto. There are numerous reports of people having lost large portions of their photo libraries, the photos then being recoverable only via hard-core utilities such as Data Rescue 3 (which of course does not recover any of your albums, ratings, titles, or the rest).

Bugs and glitches

So with all these new features, why am I not jumping up and down with excitement? One big reason: iPhoto '11 is the buggiest piece of software Apple's delivered in my memory.

Apple's support boards are overflowing with unhappy upgraders. Many claim they have lost all of their photos, which could be true in some cases. It's also possible something went wrong with the library upgrade, and the photos are there but the database has become corrupted. Reportedly Apple is working on a fix, and if true, it needs to be a fast one. Make sure you have a good backup before you install.

i figured it out! so proud of myself haha.. so anyways heres a step by step on how to get your iphoto working again and still have all of your photos, albums, ratings, faces, etc.. (IT'S VERY SIMPLE.. SHOCKED THAT NO ONE ELSE FIGURED THIS OUT BEFORE)

1) Go to the file this file that you downloaded and double click on the dmg file
2) Then in a separate window it will show you a shortcut to "install iLife" and the "readme" file
3) Right-click on the "install iLife" file and click on the option that says "show original"
4) You will then be in a folder called Packages
5) Look for the file "iPhoto.pkg" and double click on it
6) An installation  guide will come up and all you have to do is re-install it
7) Then once that has completed, go to software update and update your iPhoto
8) After that update, go to your Applications folder and click on your iPhoto - and there you have it.. your normal iPhoto!

Figured it out.. here is an easy way to get your iPhoto back!

1) Go to this downloaded file and double-click on the dmg file
2) It will then take you to a folder containing the install iLife file and the readme file
3) Right-click on the install iLife file and then click on the show original button
4) You will then be in a folder called packages
5) Look for the file that is called iPhoto.pkg and double click on it
6) Follow the installation guide and re-install iPhoto
7) Go to Software Updates and update iPhoto
8) Your iPhoto is now as good as it was before the download of this torrent.

iPhoto works but first needs the 9.1 updater. Download it from the Apple Support site and run. Now, Software Update will bring it to the current version. This must be done for it to work in Lion.
